results.name: Expansion of q * (psi(q^6) / psi(q^3))^3 * phi(q)^5 / psi(q) in powers of q where phi(), psi() are Ramanujan theta functions.
comment: Ramanujan theta functions: f(q) (see A121373), phi(q) (A000122), psi(q) (A010054), chi(q) (A000700).
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2500
Michael Somos, Introduction to Ramanujan theta functions
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Ramanujan Theta Functions
formula: Expansion of eta(q^2)^23 * eta(q^3)^3 * eta(q^12)^6 / (eta(q)^9 * eta(q^4)^10 * eta(q^6)^9) in powers of q.
G.f. is a period 1 Fourier series which satisfies f(-1 / (12 t)) = 18 (t/i)^2 g(t) where q = exp(2 Pi i t) and g() is the g.f. for A134078.
mathematica: a[ n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ 2 (EllipticTheta[ 2, 0, x^3] / EllipticTheta[ 2, 0, x^(3/2)])^3 (EllipticTheta[ 3, 0, x]^5 / EllipticTheta[ 2, 0, x^(1/2)]), {x, 0, n}]; (* _Michael Somos_, Oct 30 2015 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = my(A); if ( n<1, 0, n--; A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( eta(x^2 + A)^23 * eta(x^3 + A)^3 * eta(x^12 + A)^6 / (eta(x + A)^9 * eta(x^4 + A)^10 * eta(x^6 + A)^9), n))};
(MAGMA) A := Basis( ModularForms( Gamma0(12), 2), 58); A[2] + 9*A[3] + 31*A[4] + 45*A[5]; /* _Michael Somos_, Oct 30 2015 */
